<inglise> Commission Regulation (EC) No 1441/2001 of 16 July 2001 amending Regulation (EC) No 2848/98 in the raw tobacco sector as regards the amount to be paid to producers whose quotas for the 2001 and subsequent harvests are to be bought back </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 1441/2001, millega muudetakse tubakasektoris m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 2848/98 nendele tootjatele makstavate summade osas, kelle 2001. ja sellele j&auml;rgnevate saagiaastate kvoot tagasi ostetakse 16. juuli 2001 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2075/92 of 30 June 1992 on the common organisation of the market in raw tobacco(1), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 1336/2000(2), and in particular Article 14a thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 30. juuni 1992. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 2075/92 toortubakaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 1336/2000, (2) eriti selle artiklit 14a, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Article 36 of Commission Regulation (EC) No 2848/98 of 22 December 1998 laying down detailed rules for the application of Council Regulation (EEC) No 2075/92 as regards the premium scheme, production quotas and the specific aid to be granted to producer groups in the raw tobacco sector(3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 385/2001(4), fixes the amounts to which producers are entitled when their quotas for the 1999 and 2000 harvests are bought under the quota buy-back scheme. For the purpose of simplifying the scheme the fixing of the amounts to which producers whose quotas for the 2001 and subsequent harvests are bought back will be entitled should be made permanent by expressing those amounts as a percentage of the production premium in force during the year in which the buy-back application is submitted, this without prejudice to future amendments. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) komisjoni 22. detsembri 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2848/98 (milles s&auml;testatakse n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2075/92 kohaldamiseks &uuml;ksikasjalikud eeskirjad seoses toortubakasektori lisatasukavade, tootmiskvootide ja tootjar&uuml;hmadele antava eriabiga, (3) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (E&Uuml;) nr 385/2001 (4)) artiklis 36 kehtestatakse summad, mida tootjatel on &otilde;igus saada kvootide tagasiostmise kava raames tagasi ostetud 1999. ja 2000 saagiaasta kvootide eest; ilma et see piiraks tulevikus vastuv&otilde;etavate muudatuste kohaldamist, tuleks kava lihtsustamiseks muuta p&uuml;sivaks nende summade kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramine, millele on &otilde;igus tootjatel, kelle 2001. aasta ja j&auml;rgnevate aastate kvoodid ostetakse tagasi, v&auml;ljendades k&otilde;nealuseid summasid tagasiostmise taotluse esitamise aastal kehtiva tootmislisatasu protsendina; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) The quantities which were the subject of a quota buy-back application and the quantities bought back by group of varieties under Article 35 of Regulation (EC) No 2848/98 in respect of the 1999 and 2000 harvests were extremely small, while the average prices paid to producers for a large part of the quantities of tobacco, in particular for the group V varieties, remain extremely low, and a large proportion of the stocks of tobacco of that group remain unsold. The amounts to be paid for buy-backs from the 2001 harvest on should therefore be varied according to group of varieties and the annual buy-back amount to be paid for group V should be increased. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) kvoodi tagasiostmise taotlusega h&otilde;lmatud kogused ning m&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2848/98 artikli 35 alusel sordir&uuml;hmade kaupa tagasi ostetud kogused olid 1999. ja 2000. saagiaasta puhul erakordselt v&auml;iksed; samas on tootjatele suure osa tubakakoguste, eelk&otilde;ige V sordir&uuml;hma eest makstavad keskmised hinnad j&auml;&auml;nud &auml;&auml;rmiselt madalaks ning suur osa nimetatud sordir&uuml;hma tubakavarudest j&auml;&auml;nud m&uuml;&uuml;mata; seet&otilde;ttu tuleks alates 2001. saagiaastast tagasiostmise eest makstavaid summasid sordir&uuml;hmade l&otilde;ikes varieerida ning suurendada V sordir&uuml;hma puhul makstavat iga-aastast tagasiostmissummat; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) To prevent speculation during the 2001 harvest, for that harvest only the increased amount should be granted only to producers who have already held a quota for at least one harvest. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) spekulatsioonide v&auml;ltimiseks 2001. saagiaastal tuleks nimetatud saagi puhul anda suurendatud summa ainult nendele tootjatele, kellele on v&auml;hemalt &uuml;hel saagiaastal kvoot eraldatud; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) The measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Tobacco, </inglise>
<eesti> 4) k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;rusega etten&auml;htud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las tubakaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> In Article 36, the following subparagraphs are added to Regulation (EC) No 2848/98: "Without prejudice to future amendments, producers whose quotas for the 2001 and subsequent harvests have been bought back shall be entitled, at the time of payment of the premiums for the three consecutive harvests following the one in question, to receive each year an amount equal to a percentage of the premium referred to in Article 3(1) of Regulation (EEC) No 2075/92 applicable to the raw tobacco produced during the year of the harvest in question. </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (E&Uuml;) nr 2848/98 artiklisse 36 lisatakse j&auml;rgmised l&otilde;igud: "Ilma et see piiraks edasiste muudatuste kohaldamist, on tootjatel, kelle 2001. ja sellele j&auml;rgnevate saagiaastate kvoodid tagasi ostetakse, &otilde;igus saada k&otilde;nealusele saagiaastale j&auml;rgneval kolmel saagiaastal makstava lisatasu maksmise ajal summa, mis on v&otilde;rdne m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 2075/92 artikli 3 l&otilde;ikes 1 osutatud lisatasu protsendiga, mida kohaldatakse k&otilde;nealuse saagiaasta jooksul toodetud toortubaka suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise> That percentage shall be: </inglise>
<eesti> Selleks protsendim&auml;&auml;raks on: % </eesti>
<inglise> By derogation from the above subparagraph, producers whose quotas for the 2001 harvest have been bought back and who have held those quotas since the 2001 harvest only shall be entitled, at the time of payment of the premiums for the 2002, 2003 and 2004 harvests, to receive each year the amount referred to in the first subparagraph for the 1999 harvest. " </inglise>
<eesti> Erandina eelmisest l&otilde;igust saavad tootjad, kelle 2001. saagiaasta kvoot on tagasi ostetud ja kellele on kvoot eraldatud alles alates 2001. saagiaastast, 2002., 2003. ja 2004. saagiaasta jaoks lisatasu maksmisel esimeses l&otilde;igus osutatud 1999. saagiaasta puhul makstava summa. " </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
